The paper deals with the computation of probabilities, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The applications mentioned in the abstract also suggest a connection to computational engineering (cs.CE) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the use of bounds in the absence of complete causal knowledge may involve statistical inference (cs.SI).
